bilingual.source: Supposedly, the new movie is really good.
bilingual.target: 据说，这部新电影非常好。

bilingual.source: Supposedly, he is the best chef in town.
bilingual.target: 据说，他是镇上最好的厨师。

bilingual.source: Supposedly, he has already finished the project.
bilingual.target: 据说，他已经完成了这个项目。

bilingual.source: Supposedly, this is the most expensive restaurant in the city.

bilingual.source: Dicken's mother supposedly came from a more respectable family.
bilingual.target: 据说狄更斯的母亲来自一个更体面的家庭。

bilingual.source: The Kryptgarden? That forest is supposedly haunted!
bilingual.target: 克瑞普花园? 那森林据说是闹鬼的!

bilingual.source: The novel is supposedly based on a true story.
bilingual.target: 据说这部小说是以一个真实的故事为依据的。

bilingual.source: So this thing supposedly all correct was not all correct.
bilingual.target: 所以，这个东西据说都是正确的不正确的。

yingyinNormal.en: I've got to go. I've got to get up early. My company's testing a new steroid that supposedly doesn't shrink testicles, and the last one there has to do the measuring.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我得走了，明天我还得早起，我们公司在测试一种据说不会让睾丸缩水的新类固醇，最晚上班的人要负责测量睾丸的工作。

yingyinNormal.en: The word's "supposedly." With a "D." Maybe my mom can home school you, too.
yingyinNormal.zh: 应该是恐怕。你的发音不太标准。没准儿我妈妈也应该教教你。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, I wanna be sexy again so I'm trying to catch a cold. It should be easy, supposedly they're pretty common.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想恢复性感，所以我想感冒，应该很容易，感冒很常见。

yingyinNormal.en: No, I wasn't in a fire. And the word's "supposedly." What? You said that science is supposably really hard. Twice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没被火烧过。还有你刚刚提到恐怕。什么？你说科学课恐怕真的挺难的。说了两次呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Our friend Michael Burry found out that these mortgage bonds that were supposedly 65% AAA were actually just mostly full of shit.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的朋友迈克尔·柏利发现了这些抵押债券本应该65%都是AAA级组成，实际上大部分都是狗屎。
